claim.claim-text:
1. A method in a server computer connected over a network to a group of participants, where each participant operates a client computer, the method comprising:
receiving by the server computer a payment for each participant in the group;
associating the payments received for the group with a time period;
calculating by the server computer a designated portion of each payment to allocate to a fund;
creating the fund for the time period by combining the designated portions of the payments;
receiving by the server computer a notification for each participant in a subgroup of the group of participants, the notification indicating that during the time period an event occurred;
calculating by the server computer a portion of the fund to disburse to each participant in the subgroup; and
disbursing the fund to the participants in the subgroup, where the portion of the fund to disburse to each participant in the subgroup is a share of the fund.

10. A server computer connected over a network to a group of participants, where each participant operates a client computer, comprising:
a network interface connected to the network for communicating with each participant;
a memory device resident in the server computer; and
a processor disposed in communication with the network interface and the memory device, the processor configured to:
receive at the server computer a payment for each participant in the group;
associate the payments received for the group with a time period;
calculate at the server computer a designated portion of each payment to allocate to a fund;
create the fund for the time period by combining the designated portions of the payments;
receive at the server computer a notification for each participant in a subgroup of the group of participants, the notification indicating that during the time period an event occurred;
calculate at the server computer a portion of the fund to disburse to each participant in the subgroup; and
disburse the fund to the participants in the subgroup, where the portion of the fund to disburse to each participant in the subgroup is a share of the fund.

19. A computer-readable medium, comprising computer-executable instruction that, when executed on a server computer connected over a network to a group of participants, where each participant operates a client computer, perform the steps of:
receiving at the server computer a payment for each participant in the group;
associating the payments received for the group with a time period;
calculating at the server computer a designated portion of each payment to allocate to a fund;
creating the fund for the time period by combining the designated portions of the payments;
receiving at the server computer a notification for each participant in a subgroup of the group of participants, the notification indicating that during the time period an event occurred;
calculating at the server computer a portion of the fund to disburse to each participant in the subgroup; and
disbursing the fund to the participants in the subgroup, where the portion of the fund to disburse to each participant in the subgroup is a share of the fund.
